{
  "texts": [
    "Let bpol •/b [I, ⋅] be the category that has the same objects as bpol • [I, ⋅] and where there is a morphism between a and b if the family of all B-maps between a and b is nonempty.",
    "The identity of a is thus the family of all functions f ∶ A → A such that π a ○ f = π a.",
    "An isomorphism between a and b in this category exists if and only if there is a B-map between a and b and a B-map between b and a.",
    "We prove the first structure theorem: Theorem 3.2.15 bpol •/b [I, ⋅] Quotient on the objects.",
    "The class of p-sites is partially preordered by the relation: a → B b if and only if bpol • [I, ⋅][a, b] is non-empty."
  ]
}